"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses library scikit-learn. The issue lies in the way the ColumnTransformer is used with the Pipeline. The ColumnTransformer is correctly defined, but the GaussianNB algorithm in the Pipeline does not support the output of the ColumnTransformer which is a numpy array with more than two features for the OneHotEncoder part. GaussianNB expects non-negative feature values but OneHotEncoder outputs 0.0 or 1.0 values for each category of the categorical feature. However, the main issue here is that the numpy array outputted by the ColumnTransformer has more features than the original DataFrame because of the OneHotEncoder, but the GaussianNB does not know which of these features correspond to which of the original features. In this case, the output of the OneHotEncoder should be understood by the GaussianNB as a single categorical feature, not as multiple numerical features.\",\n  \"patch\": \"19c19,20\\n<('numeric', MinMaxScaler(), ['a']),\\n<('categoric', OneHotEncoder(), [\\\"b\\\"])\\n---\\n>('numeric', MinMaxScaler(), ['a']),\\n>('categoric', OrdinalEncoder(), [\\\"b\\\"])\\n\"\n}"